HEADWORD: Perissodactyla
<hw>Per`is*so*dac"ty*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <?/ odd (fr. <?/ over) + <?/ finger.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of ungulate mammals, including those
that have an odd number of toes, as the horse, tapir, and rhinoceros; --
opposed to <contr>Artiodactyla</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

